{{Politics of Abia State}}

The '''Abia State High Court of Justice''' is the highest and central court of [[Abia State]] located in [[Umuahia]], the state's capital city.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.channelstv.com/2015/05/06/abia-judiciary-gets-new-high-court-complex/|title=Abia Judiciary Gets New High Court Complex|work=[[Channels TV]]|date=6 May 2015|accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref> It has supreme authority than the [[Magistrate's court]]s and [[Customary court]]s in handling and determining major cases. It is headed by a [[Chief Judge of Abia State|Chief Judge]] who is appointed by the [[Governor of Abia State|Governor]] on recommendation from the [[National Judicial Council (Nigeria)|National Judicial Council]] and subject to confirmation by the [[Abia State House of Assembly]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawnigeria.com/Judicature/State%20Judicature%20and%20Judiciary/AbiaStateJudicature.html|title=Abia State Judiciary|publisher=Law Nigeria|accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref>

