{{Infobox rail line | box_width = | name = Altdorf–Flüelen tramway | color = | logo = | logo_width = | image = | image_width = | caption = | type = | system = | status = Closed and removed | locale = [[Canton of Uri]], [[Switzerland]] | start = [[Altdorf, Uri|Altdorf]] ([[Telldenkmal]]) | end = [[Flüelen]] ([[Flüelen railway station|railway station]]) | stations = 7 | routes = 1 | daily_ridership = | open = 1906 | close = 1951 | owner = | operator = | character = | depot = | stock = | linelength = {{convert|3.1|km}} | tracklength = | tracks = | gauge = [[Metre gauge|Metre]] ({{track gauge|1000mm|first=imp|disp=1}}) | minradius = {{convert|25|m}} | electrification = 600 [[Volt|V]], [[Direct current|DC]], [[Overhead lines|overhead]] | maxincline = 3.1% | racksystem = | speed = | elevation = | map = | map_state = }} [[File:Strassenbahn Altdorf-Flüelen 1906.jpg|thumb|Share of the Strassenbahn Altdorf-Flüelen AG, issued 1. February 1906]] The '''Altdorf–Flüelen tramway''' ({{lang-de|Strassenbahn Altdorf–Flüelen}}, AF) was a [[metre gauge]] electric [[tram]]way in the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[canton of Uri]]. It linked the town of [[Altdorf, Uri|Altdorf]] with [[Flüelen]], terminating adjacent to [[Flüelen railway station|Flüelen station]] on the [[Gotthard railway]].<ref name=saw23>{{cite book | title = Eisenbahnatlas Schweiz | year = 2012 | publisher = Verlag Schweers+Wall GmbH | isbn=978-3-89494-130-7 | page = 23}}</ref><ref name=ebaf>{{cite web | url = http://www.eingestellte-bahnen.ch/636/19743.html | title = Altdorf–Flüelen | language = German | work = www.eingestellte-bahnen.ch | accessdate = 2012-09-17}}</ref>
The tramway was opened in 1906, and closed in 1951, being replaced by a bus service. The line was electrified at 600 [[Volt|V]] [[Direct current|DC]]. It had a length of {{convert|3.1|km}}, with 7 stops, a maximum gradient of 3.1% and a minimum radius of {{convert|25|m}}.<ref name=saw23/><ref name=ebaf/>
The only visible remains of line is the tram depot, on the outskirts of Altdorf. After closure of the tramway, this was used as a bus depot by the [[Auto AG Uri]] until they moved to new premises in 2009.<ref name=ebaf/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.aagu.ch/unternehmen/geschichte.html | title = Geschichte | language = German |trans-title=History | publisher = Auto AG Uri | accessdate = 2012-09-17}}</ref>
