[[File:Boletice CZ CoA.gif|thumb|Coat of arms]]
The '''Boletice Military Training Area''' ('''Boletice MTA''', {{lang-cs|'''Vojenský újezd Boletice'''}}) is a military installation of the [[Czech Republic]]. It is located on {{convert|22000|ha|acre mi2}} of land in the southwest of the country, in the [[Šumava Mountains]].<ref>"[http://www.army.cz/en/ministry-of-defence/newsroom/news/belgian-soldiers-conclude-their-winter-exercise-at-czech-training-area-80483/ Belgian soldiers conclude their winter exercise at Czech training area]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6POabHg2l Archive]). [[Ministry of Defence & Armed Forces of the Czech Republic]]. Retrieved on 7 May 2014.</ref>

