'''CRI 91.9 FM''' is a radio station in [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]]. It is part of [[China Radio International]] (CRI). It broadcasts in [[English language|English]], [[Swahili language|Swahili]] and [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]]. It launched on February 27, 2006.
==Programming== The CRI programme schedule includes the "The Hot Pot Show" hosted by award winning DJ Puggy Day is a music/entertainment programme which highlights the Chinese pop music scene, and showbiz world. Listeners can also hear about tourist attractions in China, and be kept up-to-date about happening's inside CRI's two official websites. Other regular programmes are "Music Safari" and "China Now".
==References== * [https://web.archive.org/web/20081212154002/http://www.cribeyondbeijing.com/ CRI Beyond Beijing] * [http://qingting.fm/channels/1012 Live streaming]
