'''EIM Group''' (Egyptian International Motors), established in 1979 is one of [[Egypt]]’s largest privately owned entities.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.eim-eg.com/about.php |title=EIM Group|work=eim-eg.com|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref> EIM is the main business arm in the [[automotive industry]] of its parent company Alkan Group. EIM Group operates in several sectors, which includes servicing and distribution of [[automotive]] vehicles,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.targetgulf.com/MESearch/ME2/Exclusif_Egyptian_International_Motors_EIM_26345.shtml |title=Exclusif Egyptian International Motors (EIM Group) EIM Group (Egypt) imports and distributes vehicles, genuine spare parts and accessories. EIM is a distributor for Cummins (USA) and Renault (France).There are four other branches in Alexandria, Asswan, El-Arish and Monsoura. Autostrade Road, Mokkatam, El Kalaa Cairo Egypt 203770571 205065620 mmorsy.cum@eim.ie-eg.com http://www.cummins.com|work=targetgulf.com|accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> as well as the manufacturing of earth moving apparatus, utility passenger motor vehicles and [[Amphibious vehicle|marine]] to power equipment.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.alkan.com/docs/companies/default.aspx?bid=2 |title=Lines of Business|work=alkan.com|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> Eim Group is headqsuartered [[Mokattam]], [[Cairo]] and is in partnership with [[Renault]] Egypt.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.renault.com.eg/AboutRenault/AboutEIM.html |title=About EIM Group|work=renault.com.eg|quote= Mokattam, Cairo |accessdate=14 August 2012}}</ref>

Since 2006, the Egyptian International Trading & Agencies Co. established themselves as the sole distributor of [[Kia Motors]] in Egypt, which became a subsidiary of EIM Group.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.eim-eg.com/kia.php |title=EIM Group|work=eim-eg.com|quote=In 2006, the Egyptian International Trading & Agencies Co. (EIT), the sole distributor of KIA motors in Egypt, has been established as a subsidiary of EIM Group.  |accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref>

==Alkan Group==
Alkan Group was established in 1974 by Mohammed Mahoud Nosseir<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.autoarabia.org/articles/155/EIM%20&%20Renault%20Egypt%20Story%20continues%20live%20on%20Egyptian%20TV%20next%20week%20...%20... |title=EIM & Renault Egypt Story continues live on Egyptian TV next week ... Chapter One - Never pick up your car without your lawyer and police escort!|work=autoarabia.org|accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> (Chairman).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/ALKH:EY/profile |title=ALKH Profile & Executives - Alkan Holding - Bloomberg|work=bloomberg.com|accessdate=22 August 2012}}</ref> The group consists of thirteen sister companies, which range from [[Information Technology|IT]] solutions and system integrators to finance, [[investment]] consultancy and industrial spinning of cotton yarns.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.comesatradehub.com/company_details.asp?member_id=358 |title=Connecting COMESA to Global Markets|work=comesatradehub.com|accessdate=16 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.gnsegroup.com/CaseStudies/caseStudy_Alkan.aspx |title=ALKAN Holding - Case Studies|work=gnsegroup.com|accessdate=22 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=29189747 |title=Alkan Holding Co.: Private Company Information - Businessweek|work=investing.businessweek.com|accessdate=23 November 2012}}</ref>

