{{other uses}}
'''Gena''' ([[Amharic]]:ገና) or '''qarsa'''(ቃርሳ) is a traditional [[field hockey]] game popular in the [[Ethiopian highlands]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7DswAQAAIAAJ|title=Ethiopia: Off the Beaten Trail|last=Graham|first=John|date=7 September 2001|publisher=Shama Books|year=|isbn=9781931253116|location=Addis Ababa|pages=167|language=en|oclc=51553876|quote=|via=}}</ref> It is a game played in the space between villages but with no defined boundaries.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=llmCOvtWcUcC|title=Holiday Celebrations among the Highlanders of Ethiopia|last=Wolde-Georgis|first=Tsegay|date=30 November 2004|work=National Days/National Ways: Historical, Political, and Religious Celebrations around the World|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|year=|isbn=9780275972707|editor-last=Fuller|editor-first=Linda K.|location=West Port, Connecticut|pages=92, 99|language=en|oclc=547274920|quote=|via=}}</ref> It is played among two teams who attempt to throw a wooden ball in the air and hit it with sticks, the goal being to prevent the opposing team to bring the ball to their village.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rONyAAAAMAAJ|title=Queen of Sheba's heirs: cultural patterns of Ethiopia|last=Lord|first=Edith|date=1970|publisher=Acropolis Books|year=|isbn=978-0874910117|location=|pages=53|language=en|oclc=117120|quote=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/the-running-blog/2016/oct/04/two-hour-marathon-sub2hr-yannis-pitsiladis-kenenisa-bekele|title=The two-hour marathon: who is it for?|last=Crawley|first=Michael|date=4 October 2016|work=|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://archive.is/20170130171944/https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/the-running-blog/2016/oct/04/two-hour-marathon-sub2hr-yannis-pitsiladis-kenenisa-bekele|archive-date=30 January 2017|dead-url=no|access-date=30 January 2017|via=|df=}}</ref> The game is closely associated with ''Gena'' the January 7 celebration of Christmas, from which it gets its name.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nation.co.ke/oped/Opinion/Shield-Christmas-fete-from-the-perils-of-capitalist-market/440808-3497324-g8soep/|title=Shield Christmas fete from the perils of capitalist|last=Kagwanja|first=Peter|date=24 December 2016|work=|newspaper=Daily Nation|language=en-UK|archive-url=https://archive.is/20170130172015/http://www.nation.co.ke/oped/Opinion/Shield-Christmas-fete-from-the-perils-of-capitalist-market/440808-3497324-g8soep/|archive-date=30 January 2017|dead-url=no|access-date=30 January 2017|via=|df=}}</ref>

