{{Infobox Disputed Islands | plural = | name = Sabina Shoal | image name = Sabina Shoal, Spratly Islands.png | image caption = Sabina Shoal | image size = | pushpin map = South China Sea | native name = | archipelago = [[Spratly Islands]] | native name link = | other_names = | location = [[South China Sea]] | coordinates = {{coord|9|45|N|116|28|E|name=Sabina Shoal|display=inline,title}} | country claim = People's Republic of China | country 1 claim = Philippines | country 2 claim = Republic of China (Taiwan) | country = | country admin divisions title = | country admin divisions = }} '''Sabina Shoal''' ([[Filipino language|Filipino]]: ''Escoda Shoal''; {{zh|c=仙宾礁|p=Xiānbīn jiāo}}) is an [[atoll]] in the NE of [[Dangerous Ground (South China Sea)|Dangerous Ground]] in the [[Spratly Islands]], [[South China Sea]]. It is claimed by the [[People's Republic of China]], the [[Republic of China|Republic of China (Taiwan)]] and the [[Philippines]]. The Philippines puts it under the jurisdiction of [[barangay]] Pag-asa, [[Kalayaan, Palawan|Kalayaan]], [[Palawan]].<ref name=abs>{{cite news |last=Zambrano|first=Chiara |title=Mission to Ayungin shoal |url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/specials/mission-ayungin |accessdate=23 May 2014 |newspaper=ABS CBN News |date=27 March 2014}}</ref>
== Geography == Sabina Shoal lies in position 09° 45' N 116° 28' E,<ref>{{cite book |author1=D.J Hancox |author2=John Prescott|title=A Geographical Description of the Spratly Islands|publisher=International Boundaries Research Unit|location=UK|page=28}}</ref> 123.6 [[nautical miles]] from [[Palawan|Palawan Island]].<ref>{{cite web |title=PHL insists Escoda Shoal is within its sovereignty and maritime jurisdiction |url= http://balita.ph/2012/01/11/phl-insists-escoda-shoal-is-within-its-sovereignty-and-maritime-jurisdiction/|publisher=balita.ph |date= 2012-01-11 |accessdate= 2014-07-15}}</ref> It lies 56 [[nautical miles]] southwest of Carnatic Shoal, with two main parts and an area of {{convert|115|km2|mi2}}.
The eastern half of Sabina Shoal consists of reefs awash, while the western half consists of banks 3.7 to 8.3 meters deep, and reefs enclosing a [[lagoon]].<ref>{{cite book |title= Admiralty Sailing Directions - South China Sea |date=2004 |publisher=UKHO - United Kingdom Hydrographic Office |location=Taunton |page=64 |url= http://www.timawa.net/forum/index.php?topic=22679.0}}</ref>
==Disputes and controversies== In 1995, soon after occupying [[Mischief Reef]], China (PRC) installed 3 [[buoys]] near Sabina Shoal. They were confiscated by the Philippines.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bondoc |first=Jarius |title= China out to grab Zambales shoal |url= http://www.philstar.com/opinion/797147/china-out-grab-zambales-shoal |accessdate= 23 May 2014 |newspaper= Philippine Star |date= 16 April 2012}} ''(Zambales Shoal is also known as Scarborough Shoal.)''</ref>
